description:
Rojava: Syria's Secret Revolution

Sociopolitical Documentary hosted by Darius Bazargan, published by BBC broadcasted as part of BBC Our World series in 2014 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

Is the Middle East's newest country a territory called &quot;Rojava&quot;? Out of the chaos of Syria's civil war, mainly Kurdish leftists have forged a radical, egalitarian, multi-ethnic mini-state run on communal lines. But with ISIS Jihadists attacking them at every opportunity - especially around the beleaguered city of Kobane, how long can this idealistic social experiment last? Our World has gained exclusive access to Rojava, from the frontlines, to the politicians and refugee camps.

